        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:2:3:61:1",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/3/61/1",
        "text": [
          " : «مَنْ أَدْرَكَ اَلْمَشْعَرَ اَلْحَرَامَ عَلَى خَمْسَةٍ مِنَ اَلنَّاسِ فَقَدْ أَدْرَكَ اَلْحَجَّ »."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
            "Hadith.2773 - Ibn Abi Umayr narrated from Hisham ibn al-Hakam, from Abu Abdullah (as), who said: \"Whoever reaches al-Mash'ar al-Haram (the Sacred Monument) with five individuals has indeed attained Hajj.\""
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 1206,
        "local_index": 2,
        "narrator_chain": {
          "parts": [
            {
