            }
          ]
        },
        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:2:3:61:2",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/3/61/2",
        "text": [
          " : «مَنْ أَدْرَكَ اَلْمَوْقِفَ بِجَمْعٍ يَوْمَ اَلنَّحْرِ مِنْ قَبْلِ أَنْ تَزُولَ اَلشَّمْسُ فَقَدْ أَدْرَكَ اَلْحَجَّ »."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
            "Hadith.2774 - Ibn Abi Umayr narrated from Jamil ibn Darraj, from Abu Abdullah (as), who said: \"Whoever reaches the standing at Muzdalifah (Jam‘) on the Day of Sacrifice (Yawm al-Nahr) before the sun passes its zenith has indeed attained Hajj.\""
          ]
        }
      },
      {
