        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:2:3:61:3",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/3/61/3",
        "text": [
          " : «مَنْ أَدْرَكَ اَلْمَشْعَرَ اَلْحَرَامَ قَبْلَ أَنْ تَزُولَ اَلشَّمْسُ فَقَدْ أَدْرَكَ اَلْحَجَّ»."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
            "Hadith.2775 - Abdullah ibn al-Mughira narrated from Ishaq ibn Ammar, from Abu Abdullah (as), who said: \"Whoever reaches al-Mash'ar al-Haram (the Sacred Monument) before the sun passes its zenith has indeed attained Hajj.\""
          ]
        }
      },
